<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871001-0034 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:National Semiconductor Corp.</HL><DD> 10/01/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> NSM SLBTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)ELECTRIC, ELECTRONICS, APPLIANCES (ELE)JUSTICE DEPARTMENT (JUS)FEDERAL TRADE COMMISSION (FTC) </IN><TEXT>   National Semiconductor Corp., Santa Clara, Calif., said its purchase of Fairchild Semiconductor Corp. from Schlumberger Ltd., New York, has been cleared by the Justice Department and the Federal Trade Commission.    Under the previously reported purchase agreement, National Semiconductor will pay Schlumberger $122 million in stock and warrants.    National makes semiconductors and large computer systems. Fairchild makes high speed chips that are used in mainframe computers.    National stock closed yesterday at $18.375, unchanged, in New York Stock Exchange composite trading. </TEXT></DOC>